choices.text:
what are the types of verbs?
There are 12 main verb tenses in English. They can be categorized into four groups based on their function and formation rules. The categories are as follows:

1. Simple (or basic) - Present, Past, Future
2. Perfect - Present Perfect, Past Perfect, Future Perfect
3. Progressive (Continuous) - Present Continuous, Past Continuous, Future Continuous
4. Modal - Present Modals, Past Modals
